(188, 1, '2019-12-05 09:31:25', '2019-12-05 09:31:25', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MPTeq has extensive thickening and clarification experience to ensure your plant operates optimally and efficiently.&nbsp; We can ensure that your thickener is optimally sized and with flocculant and coagulant screening tests, we can identify the optimal selection of reagents.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We are able to select the correct thickener size by test work and our sizing programs assure operational flexibility and allow process upsets.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MPTeq can supply high-rate, traction, ultra-high density or paste thickeners depending on the application.&nbsp; Our specialty is high-rate, bridge-supported thickeners that can be used in light, medium, or heavy-duty applications with diameters of up to 50 m. &nbsp;CCD circuit design that allows all the CCD thickeners to be installed on a single level, drastically reducing construction cost and time also forms part of our product offering.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MPTeq also has the experience and ability to retrofit thickeners of all types from most other manufacturers.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Thickeners', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'thickeners-2', '', '', '2019-12-05 09:31:25', '2019-12-05 09:31:25', '', 0, 'https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/?page_id=188', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(189, 1, '2019-12-05 09:32:11', '2019-12-05 09:32:11', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> The MPTeq custom flocculant and reagent preparation and dosing systems are designed and fabricated as compact and robust units.  The skid-mounted flocculant plants are supplied as fully automated units, complete with a PLC set up for each specific application. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":51,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Flocculent.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-51\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Flocculant and Reagent Preparation & Dosing Systems', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'flocculant-and-reagent-preparation-dosing-systems', '', '', '2019-12-05 09:32:11', '2019-12-05 09:32:11', '', 0, 'https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/?page_id=189', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(190, 1, '2019-12-05 09:45:00', '2019-12-05 09:45:00', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Metanza Jigs are new generation designs for a mature, jigging technology.&nbsp; The leading-edge design supports a more effective recovery process and, ultimately, produces a superior concentrate while consistently delivering on lower capital and operational costs with minimum environmental impact.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Metanza Materials Handling designs and supplies new generation density separation solutions that offers the mineral processing industry a progressive approach to a technology that has been used for decades.&nbsp; On offer are a range of PLC-controlled jigs that deliver on low costs, a more effective recovery process, and a higher product yield.&nbsp; These improvements are made possible with the innovative pulse action and a unique product-gate design of the jigging equipment.&nbsp; This is complemented by a host of metallurgical engineering services that include research and development, test-work programs, plant and process design, project financing, commissioning, outsourced operations and maintenance services, and after-sales support.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Metanza jigs can be used to treat the following commodities with opportunities for treating new commodities being continuously explored:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Au</li><li>Coal</li><li>Coltan</li><li>Cr</li><li>Cu</li><li>Diamonds</li><li>Fe</li><li>Mn</li><li>Pb</li><li>Rare earths</li><li>Slags – ferrometals</li><li>Sn</li><li>Ta</li><li>W</li><li>Zn</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":54,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Jigs.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-54\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Jigs', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'jigs-2', '', '', '2019-12-05 09:45:00', '2019-12-05 09:45:00', '', 0, 'https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/?page_id=190', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(191, 1, '2019-12-05 09:47:54', '2019-12-05 09:47:54', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A larcodem (LARge COal DEnse Medium Separator) or DEMSEP (DEnse Medium SEParator) is a cylinder cyclone used in coal processing designed to beneficiate feed material sized from 0.5 mm to a top size of 150 mm, depending on the size of the DEMSEP.&nbsp; The DEMSEP circuit utilises a single circulating medium pump.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The DEMSEP offers a consistent separating density throughout its length and is classified as a zero off-set vessel.  The DEMSEP is capable of treating feeds with a wide range of product yields.  Typically, the vessel has the capacity to treat material with up to eighty percent of the feed reporting to either the sink or float outlets.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":49,\"width\":600,\"height\":451,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Demsep2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-49\" width=\"600\" height=\"451\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":48,\"width\":600,\"height\":451,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large is-resized\"><img src=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Demsep.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-48\" width=\"600\" height=\"451\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'DEMSEP\'s', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'demseps', '', '', '2019-12-05 09:48:38', '2019-12-05 09:48:38', '', 0, 'https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/?page_id=191', 0, 'page', '', 0),
