(206, 1, '2019-12-05 10:02:21', '2019-12-05 10:02:21', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Metanza Metallurgical Laboratories was established in March 2016 to assist clients in the mining and engineering services industries to conduct experimental research, process development and efficiency testing, and related specialised services.&nbsp; The Metanza laboratory combines extensive mineral processing expertise with a firm commitment to quality service through accuracy, repeatability, reliability and, technical excellence.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>All aspects of the laboratory are supervised by experienced process engineers who ensure that the test work meets a client’s specific requirements, provides a high level of strategic design in selecting process parameters, and delivers a meaningful set of data that will best position the upscaling of the process to deliver effectively.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Laboratory services includes the following:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Ore sorting</li><li>Bulk sample preparation</li><li>Milling</li><li>Gravity separation</li><li>Magnetic separation</li><li>Flotation</li><li>Settling tests in support of thickener and clarifier designs</li><li>Attritioning</li><li>Filtration</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"ids\":[55,56,38,39,37]} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery columns-3 is-cropped\"><ul class=\"blocks-gallery-grid\"><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Lab1.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"55\" data-full-url=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Lab1.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/lab1/\" class=\"wp-image-55\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Lab2.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"56\" data-full-url=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Lab2.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/lab2/\" class=\"wp-image-56\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Lab4.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"38\" data-full-url=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Lab4.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/lab4/\" class=\"wp-image-38\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Lab5.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"39\" data-full-url=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Lab5.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/lab5/\" class=\"wp-image-39\"/></figure></li><li class=\"blocks-gallery-item\"><figure><img src=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Lab3.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-id=\"37\" data-full-url=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Lab3.jpg\" data-link=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/lab3/\" class=\"wp-image-37\"/></figure></li></ul></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->', 'Laboratory Services', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'laboratory-services', '', '', '2019-12-05 10:02:21', '2019-12-05 10:02:21', '', 0, 'https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/?page_id=206', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(207, 1, '2019-12-05 10:03:14', '2019-12-05 10:03:14', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MPTeq produces a full range of attrition scrubbers from laboratory scale through to 30 m<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;suitable for scrubbing and removing inactive surface layers from minerals without the typical scale up issues that have affected other installations.&nbsp; MPTeq is dedicated to designing, manufacturing and supplying attrition scrubbers based on a thorough understanding of the process requirements.&nbsp; Our experience, expertise, and cutting edge technology allow MPTeq to provide the optimal attritioning system to suit any need.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>MPTeq’s attrition scrubbers offer advanced particle to particle interaction at the optimal velocity while minimising mechanical wear.&nbsp; This is done by completely understanding the internal slurry flow patterns and correct design of the impellers and baffles.&nbsp; We understand the operational issues pertaining to long term success of attritioning systems, so design our cells to overcome them.&nbsp; For example we have automatic dump valves that discharge the cell contents in the event of a power failure.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Features and benefits of MPTeq attrition scrubbers:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><li>Efficient impeller design</li><li>Easy drive / wet end removal</li><li>Low maintenance</li><li>Ceramic, rubber or urethane covered</li><li>No short circuiting</li><li>Automatic drain valves fitted to allow removal of solids and easy re-start</li></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":47,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Attrition-Scrubbers.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-47\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->', 'Attrition Scrubbers', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'attrition-scrubbers-2', '', '', '2019-12-05 10:03:14', '2019-12-05 10:03:14', '', 0, 'https://cmfreelancing.co.za/client_sites/MPTeq/?page_id=207', 0, 'page', '', 0),
